0% Zero-Snoop Sandbox\" message. I've designed the props for the drawer, covering state, callbacks, and data display.\n\n\n**Adding Empty State**\n\nI've just added a no-saved-blueprints state to the SovereignHistoryDrawer, which displays when there are no history items. I've designed the empty state to be visually clear and informative. I'm focusing on the visual design of the no-data state, aiming for an elegant and intuitive experience.\n\n\n**Styling the List Items**\n\nI'm now styling the list items within the SovereignHistoryDrawer to create a visually appealing and informative display. I'm focusing on key elements like the email, industry vertical, and timestamp. I'm leveraging Tailwind classes to ensure a clear visual hierarchy, responsiveness, and appropriate state indication (e.g., active vs. inactive).\n\n\n**Adding Score Display**\n\nI've just added a score display to each list item in the SovereignHistoryDrawer, using a clear visual style. I've included the score and category. The score is displayed with a white background and category in a smaller font size. I have added a reload button to reload the blueprint when pressed. The text has a subtle hover state.\n\n\n**Adding Delete Button**\n\nI'm now incorporating a delete button for each history item. I'm focusing on crafting the button with Tailwind classes to ensure it's visually clear and consistent with the rest of the design, including appropriate hover states for feedback. I'm adding an SVG icon and the button title. I'm making sure to include the onClick to call the delete function.\n\n\n"}}
